article_title: Health Insurance Exchanges And The Innovator's Dilemma--Is The Future Costovation?

article_metadata.description: It’s a heady time in the U.S. health insurance industry.  Over 30 million Americans are expected to acquire coverage as the Affordable Care Act takes effect, yet the boon of new customers is offset by a gnawing fear that profit margins will vanish.  Due to the ACA and economic pressures, [...]
